              <p><em>"We are excited to deliver our initial 28 solution on schedule"</em>, commented James Stanley, DTS Director, North America Business Unit. <em>"This major design win will enable DTS to leverage our worldwide engineering and design resources across all of our customer locations."</em></p>
              <p><em>“We are pleased that we have been able to complete this transaction ahead of schedule”, commented Todd Schnack, President &amp; CEO of DTS. “The products and services that we can now provide our increased global customer base moving forward are significantly broader. We are also now well positioned to accelerate our expansion into the key Silicon Valley market.”</em></p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="green_txt  news-heading ui-accordion-header ui-state-default ui-accordion-icons ui-corner-all" role="tab" id="ui-id-7" aria-controls="ui-id-8" aria-selected="false" aria-expanded="true" tabindex="-1"><span class="ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon ui-icon-triangle-1-e"></span>June<span class="news-span">Pete Andreyev Named to Board of Directors &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span> </h3>
            <div class="ui-accordion-content ui-helper-reset ui-widget-content ui-corner-bottom" id="ui-id-8" aria-labelledby="ui-id-7" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="true" style="display: none;">
              <p>Dynamic Test Solutions (DTS), a Singapore private limited company, has named Mr. Pete Andreyev to the company’s Board of Directors. Mr. Andreyev has 35 years of leadership experience including at multinational corporations IBM, Hitachi, and General Electric. He has served on the boards of many public and private companies, including as chairman.</p>
              <p><em>“We are excited to have an individual with Mr. Andreyev’s credentials join our board”, commented Todd Schnack, President &amp; CEO of DTS. “He brings a new perspective to DTS and his broad experience will be valuable in assisting our company to achieve our aggressive business growth objectives.”</em></p>
            </div>
